25|$|In October, 1814 Governor Macdonell sent {{notes to}} the NWC {{outposts}} {{in the region}} in the name of Lord Selkirk ordering them to abandon their posts within six months. He then raised a company of volunteer militia from the Red River settlers, armed them with muskets and appointed himself as commander. By doing so, Macdonell was <b>invoking</b> <b>the</b> <b>rights</b> of <b>the</b> Hudson’s Bay Company Royal Charter, which they felt the NWC was violating.|$|R
